The Europa League quarter-finals kick off on Monday. This year, teams that have qualified for the last eight, will play in a mini-knockout tournament in Germany. Each team plays a one-legged tie instead of the regular two for a slot in the semi-final. On Monday, Inter Milan take on Bayer Leverkusen and Manchester United face FC Copenhagen. Wolverhampton Wanderers clas with Sevilla on Tuesday, while Basel play Shakhtar Donetsk. The semi-finals will be played on August 16 and 17. MONDAY, AUGUST 10
20:00 Inter vs Bayer Leverkusen
20:00 Manchester United vs FC Koebenhavn TUESDAY, AUGUST 11
20:00 Shakhtar Donetsk vs Basel
20:00 Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Sevilla